@node DESCRIPTION

   DESCRIPTION:

   STool lets you popup existing screens just by remembering their name or

   part of their name.

   STool lets you also pop back the screens.

   STool represents the CLI-Version of <lcommand-m>. (shuffle shuffle)

@endnode

@node USAGE

   USAGE:   the following 3 ppl told me it's NOT "useage" 8)))

            Tarador (gmcalist@medusa.tor.hookup.net)
            Surak   (hudson@slb125.cc.nps.navy.mil)
            Schrade (kkrebs@netcom18.netcom.com)

            (i've always written "usage" before, just wondering...)
 
   Usage:
   STool SCREEN/M,LIST=L/S,TOFRONT=F/S,TOBACK=B/S,CONSTRING=C/S,WINSIZE=W/S
     SCREEN/M      screentitle or pattern (casesensitive!)
     LIST=L/S      list screens
     TOFRONT=F/S   bring object to front
     TOBACK=B/S    send object to back
     CONSTRING=C/S windowsize as CON:-like string
     WINSIZE=W/S   windowsize as info-string


   EXAMPLES:

   STool LIST                                  - list all open screens

   STool LIST #?i#?                            - dito but only those 
                                                 with "i" in Title

   STool TOFRONT "Public Screen: Grapevine.1"  - send GV-screen to front

   STool TOBACK  *Grape*                       - send it back again
   
   STool WINSIZE                               - tell me current window-
                                                 dimensions

   STool CONSTRING                             - window-dimensions for
                                                 batch-processing

@endnode

